    <h1>The short version</h1>
    <p class="updated">Updated July 13, 2026</p>

    <h2>The newsletter</h2>
    <p>If you subscribe, I use your email address to send The Mexico Brief. The address is sent to Beehiiv, which manages the list, confirmation email, delivery, and unsubscribe requests.</p>
    <p>I do not sell the list. You can unsubscribe from any issue.</p>

    <h2>The website</h2>
    <p>The public site does not ask for your name or create an account. A few tools, such as saved Model scenarios, use your browser's local storage. Those scenarios stay in your browser and are not uploaded by the site.</p>

    <h2>Sources and outside links</h2>
    <p>The Brief links to government agencies, news organizations, and other original sources. Their privacy practices apply when you visit them.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>If the way the site handles data changes, I will update this page and its date.</p>
